sentences: Robert Crane (born January 5, 1969 in Orange County, California) is the current bass guitarist with hard rock band Black Star Riders.
He was previously the bassist with the band Ratt.
Crane went on to work as bass technician for Bobby Dall of Poison from 1984–86.
On May 30, 2014, it was announced that Crane would be joining Black Star Riders replacing their original bassist Marco Mendoza.
In 2021 he filled in as the touring bass player for Warrant whilst Jerry Dixon took a break.
